parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
all warning lights on the dashboard illuminate
the windshield wipers activate
the radio and other electrical components malfunction
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
the ignition switch feels soft or spongy
the vehicle may not start
and the warning lights on the dashboard may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while driving
all warning lights on the dashboard illuminate
the windshield wipers activate
the radio and other electrical components malfunction
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Loss of Power Steering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and power steering can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power steering
difficulty braking
and sudden loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clockspring can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden deployment of airbag
loss of steering control
and difficulty braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Sluggish transmission
difficulty shifting gears
and loss of vehicle power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when braking, leading to a loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
especially at high speeds or when going downhill. The brakes may also make a grinding or pulsing noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes fail to respond or respond slowly
causing the vehicle to take longer to stop. The brake pads or rotors may wear out quickly
requiring frequent replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control or fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes may malfunction or fail to engage
causing the vehicle to take longer to stop or lose control. The ABS system may also malfunction
leading to unpredictable braking behavior.
